# Images: No Next.js Optimization

Do NOT transform, rewrite, proxy, or optimize image URLs using any Next.js-specific mechanism.

## Rules (strict — no exceptions)

- Always render image URLs exactly as they are stored.
- Never generate URLs containing `/_next/`, `/_next/image`, `?url=`, `w=`, `q=`, or any other Next.js image optimization parameters.
- Never wrap image URLs in any helper that modifies them.
- Do not use the Next.js `<Image>` component unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Use a standard HTML `<img>` element (or React `<img>`) for all images by default.
- Preserve the original image URL 100% without modification.
- This applies to every existing and future component, page, utility, and refactor.
- If you encounter code that uses Next.js image optimization, replace it with a normal `<img>` implementation while keeping the same styling and behavior.
- Never revert this preference unless the user explicitly instructs you to.

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ Do not use
import Image from "next/image";
<Image src={url} width={800} height={600} alt="..." />

// ✅ Use instead
<img src={url} alt="..." className="..." />
```
